Then, let us divide both sides by the coefficient of 1.27 to finally determine the X or Stock C's portfolio weight. This is computed as follows: 

$$\begin{aligned}
\dfrac{\text{1.27X}}{\text{1.27}}&=\dfrac{\text{0.4865}}{\text{1.27}}\\
&={\textbf{38.31\%}}
\end{aligned}$$

**The portfolio weight of Stock C is 38.31%.**

Next, let us compute the investment amount of the risk-free asset. We have noted in the previous items of this chapter that portfolio weight will always total to 100%. Since we have the portfolio weights of the three stocks, let us now compute the risk-free asset's portfolio weight . This is computed as follows: 


$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Risk-free asset portfolio weight}&={\text{100\% - 16.50\% - 35\% - 38.31\%}}\\
&={\textbf{10.19\%}}
\end{aligned}$$

**The risk-free asset's portfolio weight is 10.19%.**
